FBIS3-17790 "drsov061_g_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Ministers Demand Official Opinion on Legitimacy of Charges WS2903185394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1715 GMT 29 Mar 94 WS2903185394 Minsk Radio Minsk Network Language: Belarusian Article Type:BFN [Text] We have received from BELINFORM the text of a declaration signed by two deputy prime ministers and the ministers of defense, foreign affairs, and external economic relations. In this declaration, the officials reject the accusations made public by People's Deputy Alyaksandr Lukashenka in various mass media. In this regard, the declaration's authors insist that the Belarusian prosecutor general publicly make an official written assessment of the legitimacy of Lukashenka's actions, the declaration emphasized, and the accuracy of information concerned their alleged activities.
